Slurm

```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "description": "The script uses the Slurm workload manager to submit a job to a cluster. The following options are used:\n* --nodes=1: Requests one node for the job.\n* --ntasks-per-node=1: Requests one task per node.\n* --cpus-per-task=16: Requests 16 CPUs per task.\n* --mem=64GB: Requests 64GB of memory for the job.\n* --gres=gpu:1: Requests one GPU for the job.\n* -o %x-%N-%j.out: Specifies the output file name.\n* -e %x-%N-%j.err: Specifies the error file name.",
  "software_requirements": [
    "rocm-5.4.2",
    "ucx-1.13.1",
    "ompi/4.1.4",
    "singularity",
    "mpirun",
    "rochpcg"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 16,
    "memory": "64GB",
    "gpus": 1,
    "tmp_storage": "/tmp/$USER/hpcg1-$$"
  }
}
```
